goals.question: What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?
goals.rationale: This will help us understand the range and distribution of the gross revenue generated by the movies.

goals.question: What is the relationship between Production_Budget and US_Gross?

goals.rationale: This will help us understand if there is any correlation between the production budget and the revenue generated by the movies.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['US_Gross'], alpha=0.5, label='US_Gross', color='blue', bins=20)
    plt.hist(data['Worldwide_Gross'], alpha=0.5, label='Worldwide_Gross', color='green', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gross Revenue')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['Production_Budget'], data['US_Gross'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Production Budget')
    ax.set_ylabel('US Gross')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between Production_Budget and US_Gross?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['IMDB_Rating'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['IMDB_Rating'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['IMDB_Rating'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('IMDB Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of IMDB_Rating?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Running_Time_min'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Running Time')
    median_running_time = data['Running_Time_min'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_running_time, color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f'Median: {median_running_time:.2f}')
    plt.xlabel('Running Time (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Running_Time_min?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    mpaa_rating_counts = data['MPAA_Rating'].value_counts()
    ax = mpaa_rating_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of MPAA_Rating?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('MPAA Rating')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Movies')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    ax.legend(mpaa_rating_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
